"```sql\nSELECT \n    COUNT(CASE WHEN p.SEX = 'M' AND l.UA > 8.0 THEN 1 END) AS Male_Count,\n    COUNT(CASE WHEN p.SEX = 'F' AND l.UA > 6.5 THEN 1 END) AS Female_Count,\n    COUNT(CASE WHEN p.SEX = 'M' AND l.UA > 8.0 THEN 1 END) * 1.0 / \n    COUNT(CASE WHEN p.SEX = 'F' AND l.UA > 6.5 THEN 1 END) AS Male_to_Female_Ratio\nFROM \n    Patient p\nJOIN \n    Laboratory l ON p.ID = l.ID\nWHERE \n    (p.SEX = 'M' AND l.UA > 8.0) OR (p.SEX = 'F' AND l.UA > 6.5);\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the ratio of male to female patients with abnormal uric acid levels. It joins the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables on the `ID` column and filters for patients with uric acid levels above the normal range for their sex. The query counts the number of males and females with abnormal uric acid levels and calculates the ratio of these counts."